title: ASX to rise as healthy US housing data boosts markets
summary: Australian shares are set to rise as Wall Street clawed back gains after a strong showing from the US housing market.
author: Natasha Rudra

title: ASX to fall as volatility continues and virus cases top 10m
summary: Australian shares are set to drop after coronavirus cases passed 10 million around the world and a US surge sent markets into retreat.
author: Natasha Rudra

title: ASX to open higher amid choppy trading
summary: Australian shares are set to open higher as markets regained ground after early losses and uncertainty over a surge in US virus cases.
author: Natasha Rudra

title: ASX to drop as market sell-off continues
summary: Australian shares are set to fall amid a big market sell-off as virus cases surge once again in the US.
author: Natasha Rudra

title: ASX set to rise on the back of another Nasdaq high
summary: Australian shares are set to rise as markets were buoyed by stronger US economic data and another record high on the Nasdaq which gained 1.4 per cent and has only fallen twice so far in June.
author: Natasha Rudra

title: ASX set to open higher as tech stocks boost Wall Street
summary: Australian shares are looking up as Wall Street gained ground and Steve Schwarzman, chief executive officer of Blackstone Group, said the economy was likely to benefit from a V-shaped recovery.
author: Natasha Rudra

title: ASX set to drop as fallout from a seesaw week continues
summary: Australian shares are set to fall as markets feel the hangover from a volatile week on Wall Street.
author: Natasha Rudra

title: Week of uncertainty continues, leaving ASX to open flat
summary: Australian shares are set to open flat as US markets flipped and flopped in a week of continued uncertainty.
author: Natasha Rudra

title: ASX to fall slightly as US markets wobble to fourth day of gains
summary: Australian shares are set to drop as the Dow turned negative in late trading but US indexes still look set for a fourth straight day in positive territory.
author: Natasha Rudra

title: Australian shares to lift as record US retail sales drives markets
summary: Australian shares are set to rise slightly as Wall Street continued an upbeat week driven by record US retail sales data.
author: Natasha Rudra

title: ASX to rise despite second wave sell-offs
summary: Australian shares are looking up despite a sell-off in markets around the world prompted by fears of a second wave of coronavirus infections.
author: Natasha Rudra

title: ASX to rise after Wall St bounce
summary: Australian shares are set to open higher, recouping at least some of Friday's losses, after Wall Street shook off the latest sell-off.
author: Timothy Moore

title: Wall St plunges in broad sell-off
summary: The Dow dropped 1862 points, paring part of the spectacular rally that's taken place since US stocks cratered in late March.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to open lower, Nasdaq resets record high
summary: Australian shares are poised to open lower, following the Dow and S&P 500. Tech stocks were pacing Nasdaq higher again. The Fed failed to bolster Wall St.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to drop, global markets pull back
summary: Australian shares are set to ease, along with equities in Europe and the US, as investors hit pause as US central bank policymakers meet.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to rise in wake of extended US rally
summary: Australian shares are poised to rise, catching a wave of positive sentiment emanating from Wall Street. $A tops US70¢. Iron ore tops $US105/tonne.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to slip, Wall St hits pause
summary: Australian shares are poised to start the final trading day of the week quietly. US stocks modestly lower.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX set to catch global equities rally
summary: Australian shares are poised to open more than 1 per cent higher amid rising optimism about a recovery in the global economy.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to rise, GDP report awaited
summary: Australian shares are set to open higher, bolstered by the Dow and S&P 500. First quarter GDP data will be released later this morning.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to edge up, $A briefly tops US68¢
summary: Australian shares are set to edge higher, mimicking modest gains in Wall Street. However the Australian dollar powered still higher. RBA decision pending.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to slip with focus on RBA, data
summary: Australian shares are poised to open lower, but miners could extend last month's advance as iron ore retook the $US100 mark.
author: Timothy Moore
